## Summary

Updated `src/blog/people/drafts/Rose-Blackpink.md`. The fresh-eyes review was strong and mostly correct — I acted on all of it, verified the disputed facts first, and preserved everything the review flagged as working.

**Main changes:**

1. **BLACKPINK is no longer absent.** Added a group paragraph to the childhood section: she's the main vocalist, one of four faces the internet ranked daily ("the soft one" vs. Jennie/Lisa/Jisoo). This grounds the social-Four comparison wound the piece kept reaching for. Moved the "comparing myself to everyone" quote here and cut it from the Rabbit Hole so it isn't said twice.

2. **The APT. contradiction is now in play** — the sharpest tension in the review, previously unused. Her most confessional era produced her *least* confessional hit (a bouncy drinking-game duet), and the confession lives in the album cuts nobody put on the radio. Slotted in right after the No. 5 stat.

3. **Factual precision fixed.** rosie is now framed as her *first full album*, with a one-line nod to the 2021 "On The Ground" single, so a fan isn't told this is her first solo work.

